<p>France’s consumer protection agency (DGCCRF) has reported online fast-fashion platform Shein to the public prosecutor after finding listings for sex dolls described as having a &quot;childlike appearance,&quot; and has asked France’s media regulator Arcom to act, the agency said in a statement . Shein said it immediately delisted the items and launched an internal probe to determine how sellers bypassed controls . The case adds to broader EU scrutiny of Shein after a €40 million fine this year and earlier consumer-protection notices from EU authorities over pricing and sustainability claims .</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/j3U2vpFvGsrzGcpTC8zUAAKGSwt5M0PjlgJpZ119bUoOXx9ApJ5pew7RhjgfqbG-gy0owqCjISGc2wlYe9szqAi1QJkv0p_Raslj9ELo2En6vGOqmVBEtokXKEkAExE1SfbThI2rN6Rijz4hyZy6_GS4YyXfuxAAx49DLtO2YKjdPWIYCDGgGueOpDwc6eWGYDkKSjbdjPo8TjiAoZsGvCfbzYGYq0k' alt='A Shein pop-up store at a mall in Singapore, April 4, 2024.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Criminal exposure: French authorities noted that distributing child pornography via electronic communications can carry penalties including up to seven years’ imprisonment and a €100,000 fine, underlining possible criminal consequences if prosecutors pursue the case .</li><li>Content access concern: The DGCCRF flagged that pornographic items, including adult-looking sex dolls, were accessible on the platform without age-filtering measures, and it asked Arcom to ensure swift protective steps are taken .</li><li>Regulatory track record: Shein has faced recent enforcement: French authorities fined the company €40 million for misleading pricing and EU consumer authorities previously notified it over alleged fake discounts and sustainability claims .</li><li>Seller controls questioned: Shein told AFP and other outlets that the listings were removed and that an internal investigation will examine how third-party sellers managed to circumvent the platform’s control processes .</li></ul><blockquote>As a reminder, the distribution of child pornography via an electronic communications network is punishable by up to seven years’ imprisonment and a fine of €100,000. - French DGCCRF</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>French DGCCRF (consumer watchdog): The agency said it found sex dolls with childlike appearances on Shein, referred the matter to the public prosecutor and alerted Arcom to ensure proper measures are taken swiftly. (<a href='https://www.politico.eu/article/french-consumer-watchdog-reports-shein-over-childlike-sex-doll/'>Politico Europe</a>)</li><li>Shein (platform): Shein said the listings were immediately delisted and it has opened an internal investigation to determine how sellers circumvented control processes. (<a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c4gjjyvg1nqo'>BBC</a>)</li><li>European Commission / EU justice official: EU officials have already been tightening oversight of platforms like Shein and Temu, with statements signalling determination to crack down on goods that do not comply with EU rules. (<a href='https://www.politico.eu/article/french-consumer-watchdog-reports-shein-over-childlike-sex-doll/'>Politico Europe</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.france24.com/en/france/20251102-french-consumer-watchdog-reports-shein-for-selling-childlike-sex-dolls'>French consumer watchdog reports Shein for selling &#x27;childlike&#x27; sex dolls</a> - france24.com</li><li><a href='https://www.politico.eu/article/french-consumer-watchdog-reports-shein-over-childlike-sex-doll/'>French consumer watchdog reports Shein over childlike sex doll</a> - politico.eu</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/frances-anti-fraud-body-reports-shein-for-selling-childlike-sex-dolls-13947063.html'>France&#x27;s anti-fraud body reports Shein for selling &#x27;childlike&#x27; sex dolls</a> - firstpost.com</li><li><a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c4gjjyvg1nqo'>Shein accused of selling childlike sex dolls in France</a> - bbc.com</li><li><a href='h